g src=\"/assets/faces/normal/z.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/z.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/z.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"8ca9707b7381f3b1b77449db0de8b71bc204c4d3","tid":2090881,"uid":12599,"like":2,"dislike":1,"score":1,"quote":{"pid":"f0165679aa268869f439b34406fa27279ed47086","tid":2090881,"uid":143343,"like":437,"dislike":4,"score":433,"citedBy":6,"replyTime":"2020-07-02T11:33:49.000Z","msg":"褚簡寧已經違反國安法<br />\n<br />\n通過各種非法方式引發香港特別行政區居民對中央人民政府或者香港特別行政區政府的憎恨並可能造成嚴重後果。"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-07-02T13:40:40.000Z","msg":"合法寫文唔算<br />\n<br />\n貼連儂牆先算"},{"pid":"9b4fe68e3863e10255933ed0ac7b13c93ee0594d","tid":2090881,"uid":171107,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"quote":{"pid":"afff22c7decd858ed32fc3b7c75c7d7977c8d718","tid":2090881,"uid":28114,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":3,"replyTime":"2020-07-02T11:32:07.000Z","msg":"【專欄】End of Hong Kong as we know it（Michael Chugani）<br />\n<br />\nGenuine democracy is now a fool&rsquo;s dream. The reality is Beijing will make sure &ndash; through disqualification or other means &ndash; that opposition candidates won&rsquo;t win a majority of seats in September&rsquo;s Legco elections.<br />\n<br />\nIn my previous column I said Hong Kong&rsquo;s freedoms will be tested by whether the police will ban yesterday&rsquo;s annual July 1 protest. It did, despite easing of social distancing rules.<br />\n<br />\nSay goodbye to legal protests. Even when social distancing rules are lifted, the police will ban protests with the excuse they may turn violent. Western media like to headline the death of Hong Kong. That&rsquo;s inaccurate. Cities don&rsquo;t die. They exist in a different form. The accurate description should be it&rsquo;s the end of Hong Kong as we know it.<br />\n<br />\n------------------------------<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.ejinsight.com/eji/article/id/2508900/20200702-End-of-Hong-Kong-as-we-know-it\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihk